subSubSection.paragraph:
Nuchal crest composed of six, large, contiguous, lanceolate scales beginning on occiput, reaching maximum height on nape, tapering to a low, vertebral crest on body composing a single row of slightly enlarged, keeled vertebral scales extending to base of tail; body laterally compressed; dorsal body and flank scales weakly keeled, subimbricate, rectangular, arranged in indistinct, transverse, and posteroventrally oriented rows; flank scales larger than dorsal body scales; ventrals same size as dorsals; 
52
scales around midbody; scales of pectoral region, belly, and precloacal regions strongly keeled; limbs slender, covered dorsally with keeled scales; five digits on pes and manus; hind limbs larger, slightly more robust than forelimbs; subdigital lamellae of toes I, II, IV, and V bicarinate; preaxial lamellae on toe III enlarged and rounded (

Fig. 
5

); 
20
lamellae beneath fourth finger; 
25
lamellae beneath fourth toe; and tail laterally compressed, slightly swollen at base, covered with keeled scales but lacking an enlarged vertebral row, 
1.67
times SVL.
